The '''Lomas Barbudal Capuchin Monkey Project''' is an ongoing field research project founded in 1990 by [[Primatology|primatologist]] Susan E. Perry of [[University of California, Los Angeles|UCLA]].  The project is dedicated to the study of the ecology, foraging behavior, and social behavior of the [[White-headed Capuchin|white-faced capuchin monkeys]] of the [[Lomas de Barbudal Biological Reserve]] in [[Guanacaste Province|Guanacaste]], [[Costa Rica]].<ref name="Perry2012">{{Cite book | last1 = Perry | first1 = S. | last2 = Godoy | first2 = I. | last3 = Lammers | first3 = W. | doi = 10.1007/978-3-642-22514-7_7 | chapter = The Lomas Barbudal monkey project: Two decades of research on ''Cebus capucinus'' | title = Long-Term Field Studies of Primates | pages = 141–163 | year = 2012 | isbn = 978-3-642-22513-0 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref>

